        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down, Bromley, Kent</placeName>
                    <date>Mar: 29.</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>Your letter has been a great pleasure to me.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> To believe that I have interested and in any degree aided an energetic and skilful naturalist like yourself is in truth the highest reward possible to me.—</p>
<p>—I sent you a few days ago a paper on climbing plants by your brother, and I then knew for the first time that Fritz Müller was your brother.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> I feel the greatest respect for him as one of the most able naturalists living, and he has aided me in many ways with extraordinary kindess.—</p>
<p>Yours very faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

